Proposal Data Model Foundation (Build Spec)
Goal

Create a single Proposal payload that your UI can render into cards and your team can edit safely, without APIs. This is the source of truth for Proposal tab.

1) Create proposal as a first-class artifact

Add a new artifact type (or JSON object in your current store) called:

proposal_draft

It must reference:

client_id

diagnostic_id

portfolio_version_id (so proposal always ties to a locked ROI/recommendation version)

2) Proposal Payload v1 (Copy-paste JSON schema)

Use this exact structure:

{
  "proposal_id": "P-0001",
  "status": "draft",
  "client": {
    "client_id": "C-0001",
    "company_name": "ExampleCo",
    "industry": "SaaS",
    "region": "USA",
    "primary_contact": {
      "name": "—",
      "title": "COO",
      "email": "—"
    }
  },
  "linkage": {
    "diagnostic_id": "D-0001",
    "portfolio_version_id": "v4",
    "generated_from": ["diagnostic", "recommendations", "roi"]
  },
  "executive_brief": {
    "title": "AI Transformation Opportunity Brief",
    "strategic_context": "",
    "why_now": "",
    "what_success_looks_like": "",
    "positioning_statement": "We install AI systems that reduce labor, remove bottlenecks, and scale revenue, without hiring more people."
  },
  "diagnosis_blocks": [
    {
      "diagnosis_id": "DX-01",
      "title": "",
      "description": "",
      "operational_impact": ["", ""],
      "financial_impact": ["", ""],
      "evidence": [
        { "source": "questionnaire", "ref": "Q7,Q9,Q12", "note": "" },
        { "source": "ops_pattern", "ref": "PATTERN-01", "note": "" }
      ],
      "severity": "high",
      "confidence": 0
    }
  ],
  "scope_boundaries": {
    "included": ["AI readiness audit", "workflow mapping", "ROI validation", "90-day roadmap"],
    "excluded": ["guaranteed outcomes", "medical/legal/financial advice", "fully autonomous decision-making"],
    "assumptions": ["Client provides access to current tools and workflows", "Stakeholders attend validation sessions"]
  },
  "next_step_offer": {
    "offer_name": "AI Readiness & ROI Audit",
    "price": 4500,
    "currency": "USD",
    "duration": "2 weeks",
    "primary_cta": "Approve & Begin AI Audit",
    "secondary_cta": "Schedule Executive Clarification Call"
  },
  "metadata": {
    "created_at": "ISO_DATE",
    "last_updated_at": "ISO_DATE",
    "created_by": "team_user_id",
    "version": 1
  }
}

This is Phase 1 only: no solutions yet, no timelines, no team, no ROI details beyond linkage.

3) UI Cards mapped to Phase 1 fields (minimal)

Your Proposal tab should render these cards from the payload:

Executive Brief → executive_brief.*

Confirmed Diagnosis → diagnosis_blocks[]

Scope Boundaries → scope_boundaries.*

Next Step Offer → next_step_offer.*

4) Edit Rules (Important)

Team can edit only these in Phase 1:

executive_brief

diagnosis_blocks

scope_boundaries

next_step_offer.price (optional)

Everything else is read-only or system-filled.

Every edit creates a new proposal.metadata.version += 1.